.TH simple_shell 1 "January 2025" "Simple Shell" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a simple UNIX command interpreter that provides a command-line interface for users to execute commands.

The following built-in commands are supported:
.TP
.B cd [DIRECTORY]
Changes the current directory to DIRECTORY. If DIRECTORY is not specified, the home directory is used.
.TP
.B exit [STATUS]
Exits the shell with a status of STATUS. If STATUS is not specified, the exit status of the last command executed is used.
.TP
.B help
Displays information about built-in commands.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B simple_shell
Launches the simple shell.
.TP
.B cd ..
Changes the current directory to the parent directory.
.TP
.B echo "Hello, world!"
Prints "Hello, world!" to the terminal.
.TP
.B exit 0
Exits the shell with a status of 0.

